We are pleased to announce that we have a new program that partners with local and southern California TNR groups to help orphaned kittens by socializing them and finding loving homes. Big Red is one of those kittens. He is now 10 months old. He was turned into a local shelter and was going to be euthanized for being feral at only 4 months old. He is anything but. He loves kids, cats and gets along with dogs. His adoption fee is $75. He's neutered, chipped and vaccinated.

Happy Friyay from Teddy! If you are looking for a FUN puppy that will bring lots of laughs and good times to your life, then Teddy is your boy! Teddy is a bold little adventurer. He is the first to try new things whether it is learning to climb stairs or running through puddles. Boy, does he love a good puddle! His foster mom says he has two modes: play and sleep. He delights the kids in his foster home with his silly antics. He is always up for a game of tug or chase with his brother Tipper or one of the other dogs in the house. Teddy's mama is a Lab/Boxer mix which is where he got his beautiful brindle coat. His dad is a mystery, but it is obvious that he will be a big boy (Just look at that paw! But then, it IS the closest to the camera). Teddy was born in early December and he is vaccinated, neutered, micro-chipped, and ready for his forever family. Please contact forgottenpetadvocates@yahoo.com to meet him!

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Jambo! This sweet love bug is a 6-year old Golden Retriever/Basset hound mix. Jambo is a social butterfly and wants to be by your side. Jambo is a super chill boy that loves to spend his days lounging and playing with his foster family. He walks well on leash and loves a good game of fetch! He is great with kids and everyone he meets. His goofy personality is sure to win you over. This awesome guy is ready to find his forever home! He will weigh around 50lbs after gaining some much needed weight. He is house trained, neutered, current on vaccines and microchipped.
